      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is very important that you **do not** stop taking sertraline or switch to St. John's Wort without talking to your prescribing doctor. These two substances can interact dangerously, potentially causing serotonin syndrome. Nausea and feeling wired are side effects that your doctor can help manage with dosage adjustments or other options. Please contact your healthcare provider to discuss these side effects safely.",
