      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While reducing your dose might seem like a gradual taper, this self-adjustment is still dangerous because it changes the timing and interaction of medications unpredictably. St. John's Wort significantly impacts how your body processes serotonin, which can be toxic when combined with residual sertraline in your system. Please consult a pharmacist or an urgent care clinic instead if your primary doctor is unavailable to get professional, immediate guidance.",
